6/23/22, 6:39 PM - +94 75 237 3502: Dear Students, Your assignment test 01 of Mathematics will be held on Friday (24.06.2022) at 9.00am via online. This assignment is based on vectors & complex numbers. Procedures to do the Assignment exam via online (i) Login to MsTeams (Please let us know if you are not in the member of 2022_MC1020 group) (ii) We will create the assignment on 9.00am. After that you can see the Assignment tab in the chat. If Click the assignment Icon, then you can view the assignment paper. iii) Write your answers in your own answer sheet with in the allocated time period. (60 minutes) (iii) After completing your answers take a clear photo of your answers and convert your photos into pdf file (It is better to use Camscaner or related software which can convert the photo in to pdf) (v) Then upload your answers in the assignment tab in the teams. (We will give 30 minutes for scanning and uploading) Total Duration 60 minutes - writing your answers 30 minutes - Scanning and uploading Total: 90 minutes Teams will notify your late submission if you will upload your answers after 10.30 am Thanks, Best Regards, S.Thawsika

Message from the ESU Drawing Committee 

Those who have lost or damaged their set squares while using must purchase and hand over *sets squares of the same brand* at the end of the semester. 

If anyone have lost or damaged their *tool boxes or tools* while using, please inform us. 

*All drawing equipment must be handed over at the end of the semester.*

Please use your drawing tools with care. The tools are really expensive and fines will have to be paid for any damages.

භාවිතා කරන අතරතුර තම විහිදී චතුර්ස්‍ර නැතිවූ හෝ හානි වූ අය සෙමෙස්ටරය අවසානයේ *එම සන්නාමයේම විහිදී චතුර්ස්‍ර* මිලදී ගෙන භාර දිය යුතුය.

.

📍Faculty Environment,

.

.

.

.

.

Thank you.

11/23/22, 11:04 PM - Ravindu Dinelka: 🛑🛑🛑
Dear Executive committee,

Students Union is something big and has very serious issues to address. Everyone should follow the right steps to solve issues, and for all little little issues and problems don't use the names of ESU or ask President or Secretary to interfere and solve them. If Union is involved in all these little things the prestige of Union will be decreased. So try to solve everything in lower boundaries or contact all the possible people you can get the solution. And let the union takes care of very serious issues,  problems and developments. 

Like if there are any issues in a hostel, the hostel committee should take action. Students have to force them to take action. Don't inform ESU to take action. And if you want ESU to take any action inform us of the whole details transparently. Then we can decide whether to take action or not. 

If there are any issues try to approach them in these stages, 
1. Individual Appeal  
2. Students Appeal  
3. Batch representative ( For Faculty issues only) 4. ESU representative ( For Faculty issues only)
5. Specific Committee President/ Secretary 

 *Then only approach the Union President/ Secretary.* 

Please consider these things in the future and behave responsibly.

Thank you.

Guys please update this list about the topics you select for the project to avoid  submission of same topic. 

1. AX1 - Proper Medical waste  disposal in Kilinochi general hospital

2. AX2 - Assessment of water quality in water resource in Jaffna Area.

3.AY3-Municipal solid waste management

04.CY1 - To ascertain the quality of water sources in a galewela area

05. AY4- Comparative study of color removal from drinking water using cheap/waste materials

06-Dx4 wastage management in garments in kilinochi permisses and surrounding areas

07-Dx2- complete waste assessment and management system in University of jaffna Kilinochchi premises

08- DX1 - Ocean pollution at coastline areas

09- AY2 - water pollution in rivers and canels in anuradhapura area

10. BX1- Prevention of environmental pollution  caused by pesticides used in agriculture

11- BX4-waste water treatment in kilinochi

12-CY3 - Soil erosion in nearby waterbodies

13-CY4-Water assessment and CKD analysis of anuradhapura region

14. Environmental pollution due to Industries in jaffna

15- BY2 -  Waste management and recycling of them in MAS and KIST

16.Cx4-To reduce the plastic wastages in university area.

17- DY4 - Analysis of medical waste disposing techniques in Anuradhapura general hospital.

18.DY3 Soil erosion of beach side from wennappuwa to chilaw

19. Dx3-Marine pollution due to solid waste

20-AY1-Analsis of coral reef  and Mangrove ecosystem destruction happens around  southern costal area

21. BY4 - Management of sewage instead of directly discharging it into railway tracks.

22.AX4-Dambulla Compost Plant

23- Cx3 - Waste management in faculty of engineering University of Jaffna

24- BY3-water problems faced by students in university

25.DY2- Medical waste and waste water management in Vavuniya general hospital.

26. BY1 - Solid waste management under the heavy metals.

27. Dy1 - Deforestation all over the country

28. CY2 - Garbage dump disposal around Anuradhapura area

කාලෙකට පස්සේ එන නිවාඩුවකට උනත් ගෙදර යන්නේ නැති කෙනෙක්ගෙන් ඒ ඇයි අහන්න එපා!

හුගක් කල් ආදරේ නොකර තනියම ඉතුරු කාලෙත් ඉන්න හිතන් ඉන්නවා කියලා කෙනෙක් කිව්වොත් ඒ ඇයි අහන්න එපා!

හැමෝටම වැඩකට යනවා කියලා ගිය යාලුවා තනියම coffee shop එකක කෝපි එකක් බොනවා දැක්කොත් ” ඇයි මචං තනියම? කියලා අහන්න එපා!

අසීමිතව පොත් වලට ඇබ්බැහි උන කෙනෙක්ගෙන් " මචං ilm එකක් එහෙම try කරපන්” කියන්න එපා!
කෙනෙක් එයාගෙ කතාවම ඔයාට කියනවා නම්, ඒ කතාව සම්භන්දව තීරණ ගන්න එපා ! අහන් විතරක් ඉන්න!

කෙල්ලෙක් කොල්ලෙක් හින්දා මානසිකව වැටිලා ඉන්න කෙනෙක්ට,

" අපෝ බලහන්, වෙන ඉන්ට තියෙන ප්‍රශ්න එක්ක බලද්දි ඕවා මොනවද ? කියලා නම් කියන්නම එපා!

අවුරුදු ගානකින්වත් අලුත් ඇදුමක්වත් ගන්නේ නැති යාලුවට " හෙන ලෝබයිනේ බං ” කියන්න එපා!

30,000 ක් පඩි ගන්න කෙනෙක්ගේ ෆෝන් එකේ වෝල්පේපර් එකේ ‘BMW එකක් තියෙනවා දැකොත් හිනා වෙන්න එපා!

අවුරුදු දෙකකට විතර පස්සෙ හොදම යාලුවෙක්ගෙන් කෝල් එකක් ආවම "
 සෑහෙන කාලෙකින් මොකෝ මේ උබට දැන් හරි ගිහින් නේ. පට්ට ලොකුකම ආ උබේ” කියලා අහන්න එපා!

කොටින්ම කිව්වොත්, කවදාවත් කාගෙන්වත් එයාල කියන දේට අමතරව දෙයක් අහන්නම එපා!

මිනිස්සු කියන්නේ වචන කරගන්න පුලුවන්

දේවල් විතරයි ! වචන කරගන්න බැරි දේවල් නිදහස් කරගන්න, තමන්‍ගේ විදියක් හැම මනුස්සයටම තියෙනවා!

ඒවා එක්ක ඒ මිනිස්සුන්ට ඉන්න දෙන්න!

මිනිස්සුන්ගේ පුරුදු ගැන ප්‍රශ්න කරන්න එපා! දන්න දේවල් වලින් මිනිස්සු ගැන තීරන ගන්න එපා! මිනිස්සුන්ට දේවල් කියන්නත්, නොකියන්නත් හේතු තියනවා!
 "හැමෝටම හැමදේටම හේතු තියෙනවා !"

ප්‍රශ්නාර්ත නැති නිදහස් මනුස්සයෙක් වෙන්න! උදේ හවා අපි මේ දකින්නේ, ජීවිතේ එක එක

 Don't ask someone who doesn't go home even for a vacation that comes after a while!

 If someone says that they are thinking of being alone for the rest of their lives without love, don't ask them why!

 If you see the friend who told everyone to go to work drinking coffee alone in a coffee shop, why is he alone?  Don't ask!

 Don't ask someone who is addicted to books, "Dude, try an ilm like that"!
 If someone tells you his story, don't make decisions based on that story!  Just listen!

 For someone who is depressed because of a girl or a boy,

 "Look, what are these problems when you look at them?" Don't tell me!

 Don't say "Hena Lobaine Bang" to a friend who hasn't bought new clothes in years!

 Don't laugh if you see a BMW on the wallpaper of someone who earns 30,000!

 After about two years, a call came from a best friend.
  It's been a long time and now you've got it right.  Don't ask that you are so big!

 In short, never ask anyone anything other than what they say!

 People can say words

 Only things!  To free things that cannot be put into words, every person has his own way!

 Let those people be with them!

 Don't question people's habits!  Don't make decisions about people based on what you know!  People have reasons for saying and not saying things!
  "Everyone has a reason for everything!"

 Be a free man without question!  Morning and evening we see this, one life at a time

 People who bet with the seasons!

 So

 "Let the people be at a loss"

1/22/23, 9:37 AM - Salmaan: Important shortcut keys for computer..
CTRL+A. . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . Select All
CTRL+C. . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . Copy
CTRL+X. . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . Cut
CTRL+V. . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . Paste
CTRL+Z. . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . Undo
CTRL+B. . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . Bold
CTRL+U. . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . Underline
CTRL+I . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . Italic
F1 . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . Help
F2 . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . Rename selected object
F3 . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . Find all files
F4 . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . Opens file list drop-down in dialogs
F5 . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . Refresh current window
F6 . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . Shifts focus in Windows Explorer
F10 . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . Activates menu bar options
ALT+TAB . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . Cycles between open applications
ALT+F4 . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . Quit program, close current window
ALT+F6 . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . Switch between current program windows
ALT+ENTER. . . . . . . . . . . . . . Opens properties dialog
ALT+SPACE . . . . . . . . . . . . . . System menu for current window
ALT+¢ . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . opens drop-down lists in dialog boxes
BACKSPACE . . . . . . . . . . . . . Switch to parent folder
CTRL+ESC . . . . . . . . . . . . . . Opens Start menu
CTRL+ALT+DEL . . . . . . . . . . Opens task manager, reboots the computer
CTRL+TAB . . . . . . . . . . . . . . Move through property tabs
CTRL+SHIFT+DRAG . . . . . . . Create shortcut (also right-click, drag)
CTRL+DRAG . . . . . . . . . . . . . Copy File
ESC . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . Cancel last function
SHIFT . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . Press/hold SHIFT, insert CD-ROM to bypass auto-play
SHIFT+DRAG . . . . . . . . . . . . Move file
SHIFT+F10. . . . . . . . . . . . . . . Opens context menu (same as right-click)
SHIFT+DELETE . . . . . . . . . . . Full wipe delete (bypasses Recycle Bin)
ALT+underlined letter . . . . Opens the corresponding menu
PC Keyboard Shortcuts
Document Cursor Controls
HOME . . . . . . . . . . . . . . to beginning of line or far left of field or screen
END . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . to end of line, or far right of field or screen
CTRL+HOME . . . . . . . . to the top
CTRL+END . . . . . . . . . . to the bottom
PAGE UP . . . . . . . . . . . . moves document or dialog box up one page
PAGE DOWN . . . . . . . . moves document or dialog down one page
ARROW KEYS . . . . . . . move focus in documents, dialogs, etc.
CTRL+ > . . . . . . . . . . . . next word
CTRL+SHIFT+ > . . . . . . selects word
Windows Explorer Tree Control
Numeric Keypad * . . . Expand all under current selection
Numeric Keypad + . . . Expands current selection
Numeric Keypad – . . . Collapses current selection
¦ . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . Expand current selection or go to first child
‰ . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . Collapse current selection or go to parent
Special Characters
‘ Opening single quote . . . alt 0145
’ Closing single quote . . . . alt 0146
“ Opening double quote . . . alt 0147
“ Closing double quote. . . . alt 0148
– En dash. . . . . . . . . . . . . . . alt 0150
— Em dash . . . . . . . . . . . . . . alt 0151
… Ellipsis. . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . alt 0133
• Bullet . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . alt 0149
® Registration Mark . . . . . . . alt 0174
© Copyright . . . . . . . . . . . . . alt 0169
™ Trademark . . . . . . . . . . . . alt 0153
° Degree symbol. . . . . . . . . alt 0176

Ctrl + End Go to end of document

Shift + End Highlight from current position to end of line

Ctrl + g Move one word to the right at a time

applications

Key
Automatically adjust widths of all columns
in Windows Explorer

or program

During Bootup
Boot safe mode or bypass system files

During Bootup
When putting in an audio CD, will prevent

and WINKEY + D

Display the search for computers window

Pause /Break

விண்ணப்பிக்க உதவுங்கள் 👇

💥இவ் விண்ணப்பப் படிவத்தை நிரப்பும் போது Colour விண்ணப்படிவத்தில் நிரப்பவும்.

நாளை மறுதினம் நடைபெறவிருக்கும் இரத்த தான முகாமுக்கான இரத்த தான வழங்குனர்களின் எதிர்பார்க்கை தொகை இன்னும் கிட்டவில்லை.

Introducing Past Master: The Ultimate Study App for Advanced Level School Students

We are excited to present Past Master, the ultimate study app designed specifically for Sinhala, Tamil and English medium advanced level school students. With its comprehensive features and user-friendly interface, Past Master aims to revolutionize the way students prepare for their exams by providing access to past papers year-wise and unit-wise. We would like to take this opportunity to share the app's exciting features and benefits, encouraging its adoption within your educational community.

Key Features of Past Master:

1.MCQ Challenge Mode: Past Master offers an engaging MCQ challenge mode that allows students to tackle past papers year-wise and unit-wise. Students can select specific years and units to focus on, enabling them to tailor their practice sessions according to their individual needs and areas of improvement.

2.Performance Analysis: Past Master provides detailed performance analysis for each MCQ challenge attempted. Students can review their performance on a year-wise and unit-wise basis, gaining insights into their strengths and weaknesses in specific subjects and topics. This analysis empowers students to 

3.Comparative Analysis: The app includes a comparative analysis feature that allows students to benchmark their performance against their district-wise peers or island-wise students. This feature not only fosters healthy competition but also provides students with a sense of their relative strengths in comparison to their peers.

4.Vast Repository of Past Papers: Past Master boasts a vast collection of past papers, conveniently organized year-wise and unit-wise. This extensive database ensures that students have access to a wide range of practice material, allowing them to thoroughly prepare for their exams and gain confidence in each subject.

5.User-Friendly Interface: The app is designed with a user-friendly interface, making it intuitive and easy to navigate. Students can effortlessly select specific years, units, and subjects to access the corresponding past papers and MCQ challenges. The interface promotes a seamless and enjoyable study experience.

6.User Contributions: Past Master encourages active participation from users by allowing them to contribute their own past papers to the app. This collaborative approach ensures that the app remains updated with the latest papers, offering a dynamic and ever-growing collection for students. Users can contribute their past papers, thereby fostering a sense of community and shared knowledge.

7.Completely Free and Ad-Free: We are delighted to inform you that Past Master is a completely free app with no hidden charges or in-app purchases. We believe that every student should have access to quality education resources without any financial burden. Moreover, the app is ad-free, ensuring a distraction-free study environment for students.
6/25/23, 2:24 PM - Faham: Past Master
Download link:

හඳුන්වාදෙන Past Master: උසස් පෙළ පාසල් සිසුන් සඳහා වූ හොඳම අධ්‍යාපන යෙදුම

 සිංහල, දෙමළ සහ ඉංග්‍රීසි මාධ්‍ය උසස් පෙළ පාසල් සිසුන් සඳහා විශේෂයෙන් නිර්මාණය කර ඇති අවසාන අධ්‍යාපන යෙදුම වන Past Master ඉදිරිපත් කිරීමට අපි සතුටු වෙමු. එහි විස්තීර්ණ විශේෂාංග සහ පරිශීලක-හිතකාමී අතුරුමුහුණත සමඟින්, Past Master හි අරමුණ වන්නේ වසර අනුව සහ ඒකක අනුව පසුගිය ප්‍රශ්න පත්‍ර සඳහා ප්‍රවේශය ලබා දීමෙන් සිසුන් තම විභාග සඳහා සූදානම් වන ආකාරයේ විප්ලවීය වෙනසක් ඇති කිරීමයි. ඔබගේ අධ්‍යාපනික ප්‍රජාව තුළ එය භාවිතා කිරීම දිරිගන්වමින් යෙදුමේ ආකර්ෂණීය විශේෂාංග සහ ප්‍රතිලාභ බෙදා ගැනීමට අපි මෙය අවස්ථාවක් කර ගැනීමට කැමැත්තෙමු.

Past Master ප්‍රධාන​ ලක්ෂණ:

1.MCQ Challenge Mode: Past Master විසින් සිසුන්ට පසුගිය ප්‍රශ්න පත්‍ර වසර අනුව සහ ඒකක අනුව විසඳීමට ඉඩ සලසන ආකර්ෂණීය MCQ අභියෝග මාදිලියක් ඉදිරිපත් කරයි. සිසුන්ට අවධානය යොමු කිරීම සඳහා නිශ්චිත වසර සහ ඒකක තෝරා ගත හැකි අතර, ඔවුන්ගේ පුද්ගල අවශ්‍යතා සහ වැඩිදියුණු කිරීමේ ක්ෂේත්‍ර අනුව ඔවුන්ගේ පුහුණු සැසි සකස් කරගැනීමට​ ඔවුන්ට හැකි වේ.

2.Performance Analysis: Past Master විසින් උත්සාහ කරන සෑම MCQ අභියෝගයක් සඳහාම සවිස්තරාත්මක කාර්ය සාධන විශ්ලේෂණයක් සපයයි. නිශ්චිත විෂයයන් සහ මාතෘකා තුළ ඔවුන්ගේ ශක්තීන් සහ දුර්වලතා පිළිබඳ අවබෝධයක් ලබා ගනිමින් සිසුන්ට ඔවුන්ගේ කාර්ය සාධනය වසර අනුව සහ ඒකක අනුව සමාලෝචනය කළ හැකිය. 

3.Comparative Analysis: යෙදුමට සංසන්දනාත්මක විශ්ලේෂණ විශේෂාංගයක් ඇතුළත් වන අතර එමඟින් සිසුන්ට ඔවුන්ගේ දිස්ත්‍රික් අනුව සම වයසේ මිතුරන්ට හෝ දිවයින අනුව සිසුන්ට එරෙහිව ඔවුන්ගේ කාර්ය සාධනය මිණුම් සලකුණු කිරීමට ඉඩ සලසයි. මෙම විශේෂාංගය සෞඛ්‍ය සම්පන්න තරඟකාරීත්වයක් ඇති කරනවා පමණක් නොව සිසුන්ට ඔවුන්ගේ සම වයසේ මිතුරන්ට සාපේක්ෂව ඔවුන්ගේ සාපේක්ෂ ශක්තීන් පිළිබඳ හැඟීමක් ද ලබා දේ.

4..Vast Repository of Past Papers: Past Master සතුව වසර අනුව සහ ඒකක අනුව පහසු ලෙස සංවිධානය කරන ලද අතීත ලිපි ලේඛන විශාල එකතුවක් තිබේ. මෙම පුළුල් දත්ත සමුදාය සිසුන්ට ඔවුන්ගේ විභාග සඳහා හොඳින් සූදානම් වීමට සහ එක් එක් විෂයයන් කෙරෙහි විශ්වාසයක් ඇති කර ගැනීමට ඉඩ සලසමින් පුළුල් පරාසයක පුහුණු ද්‍රව්‍ය සඳහා ප්‍රවේශය සහතික කරයි.

5.User-Friendly Interface: යෙදුම නිර්මාණය කර ඇත්තේ පරිශීලක-හිතකාමී අතුරුමුහුණතක් සමඟින්, එය බුද්ධිමය සහ පරිශීලනයට​ පහසු කරයි. අදාළ අතීත ප්‍රශ්න පත්‍ර සහ MCQ අභියෝගවලට ප්‍රවේශ වීමට සිසුන්ට නිශ්චිත වසර, ඒකක සහ විෂයයන් පහසුවෙන් තෝරා ගත හැකිය. අතුරු මුහුණත බාධාවකින් තොරව සහ විනෝදජනක අධ්‍යයන අත්දැකීමක් ප්‍රවර්ධනය කරයි.

6.User Contributions: Past Master විසින් ඔවුන්ගේම අතීත ලිපි ලේඛන යෙදුමට දායක කිරීමට ඉඩ දීමෙන් පරිශීලකයින්ගෙන් සක්‍රීය සහභාගීත්වය දිරිමත් කරයි. මෙම සහයෝගී ප්‍රවේශය සිසුන් සඳහා ගතික සහ දිනෙන් දින වර්ධනය වන එකතුවක් ඉදිරිපත් කරමින් නවතම පත්‍රිකා සමඟ යෙදුම යාවත්කාලීනව පවතින බව සහතික කරයි. පරිශීලකයින්ට ඔවුන්ගේ අතීත ලේඛනවලට දායක විය හැකි අතර එමඟින් ප්‍රජාව පිළිබඳ හැඟීමක් සහ බෙදාගත් දැනුම පෝෂණය කළ හැකිය.

7.Completely Free and Ad-Free: Past Master යනු සැඟවුණු ගාස්තු හෝ යෙදුම තුළ මිලදී ගැනීම් නොමැතිව සම්පූර්ණයෙන්ම නොමිලේ යෙදුමක් බව ඔබට දැනුම් දීමට අපි සතුටු වෙමු. සෑම සිසුවෙකුටම මූල්‍යමය බරක් නොමැතිව ගුණාත්මක අධ්‍යාපන සම්පත් සඳහා ප්‍රවේශය තිබිය යුතු බව අපි විශ්වාස කරමු. එපමනක් නොව, යෙදුම දැන්වීම්-රහිත වේ, සිසුන් සඳහා බාධාවකින් තොර අධ්‍යයන පරිසරයක් සහතික කරයි.

தமிழ், சிங்கள மற்றும் ஆங்கில மொழி மூலம் உயர்தரம் கற்கும் மாணவர்களுக்காக பரீட்சையை வெற்றிகரமாக எதிர்கொள்ளும் நோக்கில் கடந்தகால பரீட்சை வினாத்தாள்களை இலகுவான முறையில் அணுகும் விதமாக Past Mater Application வடிவமைக்கப்பட்டுள்ளது.

முதற்கட்டமாக உயிரியல் விஞ்ஞான துறை, மற்றும் பௌதீகவியல் விஞ்ஞான துறை மாணவர்களுக்காக உருவாக்கப்பட்டுள்ளது. எதிர்வரும் காலங்களில் ஏனைய துறைகளுக்கும்
வடிவமைக்க திட்டமிடப்பட்டுள்ளது.

 Past Mastar Application மாணவர்களுக்கு எவ்வாறு உதவுகின்றது??
 
1.MCQ Challenge Mode ஐ பயன்படுத்தி மாணவர்களை இறுதிப் பரீட்சைக்கு தயாராகும் விதத்தில் இரண்டு மணி நேரத்திற்குள் 50 வினாக்களை செய்து விடையளிப்பதற்கு
இடமளிக்கின்றது.

2. மாணவர்கள் அலகு ரீதியாக MCQ வினாக்களை செய்வதற்கான வசதிகளை கொண்டுள்ளது.

3. கடந்த கால வினாப்பத்திரங்களை பதிவிறக்கம் ( Download) செய்து கொள்ள முடியும்.

4. Performance Analysis - Mcq வினாக்களை செய்வதன் மூலம் ஒவ்வொரு அலகுக்குமான பகுப்பாய்வை வழங்குகின்றது இதனூடாக மாணவர்கள் எந்த அலகில் முன்னேற்றம் அடைந்துள்ளோம் என்பதையும் எந்த அலகில் கூடிய கவனம் செலுத்த வேண்டும் என்பதையும் தெளிவாக காட்டுகிறது

5.Past Master இல் ஒப்பீட்டு பகுப்பாய்வு அம்சம் உள்ளது.  இதன் மூலம் மாணவர்கள் தங்கள் செயல்திறனை மாவட்ட ரீதியாகவோ, தேசிய ரீதியாகவோ Rank முறை மூலம் ஒப்பீடு செய்ய முடியும்.

6.User friendly interface-
இது மிகவும் எளிதாக பயன்படுத்தக் கூடிய வகையில் வடிவமைக்கப்பட்டுள்ளது. எந்தவித சிரமமுமின்றி கேள்விகளை அணுக முடியும்

7.பயனர் பங்களிப்புக்கள் -Past Master users தங்களிடம் இருக்கும் கடந்த கால வினாப்பத்திரங்களை Past Master இல் upload செய்ய இடமளிக்கின்றது.

8. Past Master App முற்றிலும் இலவசமானது. எந்தவித விளம்பரங்களும் அற்றது. மாணவர்கள் எவ்வித சிரமமும் இன்றி இந்த App  ஐ பயன்படுத்த முடியுமான விதத்தில் வடிவமைக்கப்பட்டுள் ளது.

Subject: Explanation for Not Meeting 80% Attendance Requirement

Dear [Professor's Name],

I hope this letter finds you in good health and high spirits. I am writing to address my current attendance record in your lectures and to provide an explanation for falling short of the 80% attendance requirement.

First and foremost, I would like to express my sincere apologies for not meeting the attendance expectation. I understand the importance of attending lectures regularly, and I regret that my attendance has been below the desired level. However, I would like to outline the circumstances that have contributed to this situation.

Health Issues: Unfortunately, during the semester, I have been dealing with a persistent health issue that has hindered my ability to attend lectures consistently. Despite my best efforts to manage my health, there were days when attending class was physically challenging, and I needed to prioritize my recovery.

Family Emergency: A few weeks ago, my family faced an unexpected emergency that required my immediate attention and support. I had to be present and provide assistance during this difficult time, which resulted in me missing several lectures.

Personal Obligations: I am also actively involved in extracurricular activities and community service, which sometimes clash with my lecture schedule. These commitments are essential to my personal growth and contribute to my overall development, but they occasionally result in conflicts that prevent me from attending lectures.

Prioritizing Coursework: As a conscientious student, I have consistently dedicated significant time outside of class to study the course material thoroughly. Although attending lectures is undeniably valuable, I have ensured that I remain up to date with the curriculum by seeking alternative resources and engaging with fellow students to fill in any knowledge gaps.

I genuinely value the education I am receiving at [University Name] and recognize the significance of attending lectures to maximize my learning experience. I understand that regular attendance fosters an active and participatory classroom environment, and I assure you that I am committed to improving my attendance moving forward.

In light of the aforementioned circumstances, I kindly request your understanding and leniency regarding my attendance record. I would be grateful for any assistance or guidance you can provide to help me catch up on missed material and to ensure that I am on track with the course requirements.

Thank you for your attention and understanding. I appreciate your commitment to delivering quality education and for considering my situation. If there is any further information or documentation you require, please do not hesitate to contact me. I look forward to discussing this matter with you and finding a suitable solution.

Yours sincerely,

[Your Name]

▪️We have noticed that most of the students are using canteen and juice bar for studying purpose.

▪️You can use but beacuse of Lack availability of furnitures , other students are struggling to get their lunch/breakfast in peak time.

▪️So for the convenience of students hereby we are requesting all to follow below mentioned regulations.

*(APPLICABLE TO STUDENTS FROM ALL 3 FACULTIES)*

▪️Students should not use the canteen & Juice bar other than refreshment purpose specially in the peak time & working hours.

▪️For the agriculture canteen.
 Morning 7.00 am - 9.00 am
Noon 12.00 - 2.00 pm

▪️For the juice bar  
7.00 am-5.30 pm  (Monday - Saturday )

▪️Other than working hours you can use these places for study purpose.

▪️Table should be cleaned after finishing your meal.

▪️You can't keep your empty plates or glass bottles or other used materials on the table while you are leaving.

▪️keep it in the allocated places and properly dispose the waste materials in dustbins.

▪️A Line should be maintained for getting your meal.

▪️Places allocated for staffs should not be used by students. 
*(Make a serious note on this)*

▪️Avoid re-arranging the furnitures in both places .

▪️Violating the rules is a punishable offence, 
Your violation will be notified to your respective faculties with a proof .

Informed by :- 
*SAR/Faculty of Agriculture*

- Your regards
*Students' union, Faculty of Agriculture*💚

9/13/23, 9:45 PM - Didula (පොටේ) Aiya E21 UOJ: Calling for Volunteer Undergraduates: Apeksha Hospital Energy Audit Initiative

Dear Enthusiastic Engineering Undergraduates,

The Electrical, Electronic, and Telecommunication Engineering Sectional Committee (EETESC) of IESL is embarking on an exciting journey to conduct a complimentary walkthrough energy audit at Apeksha Hospital, Maharagama.

Given the absence of essential electrical layout drawings at the hospital, we've taken the initiative to assemble a dedicated team of volunteer university undergraduates to tackle this challenge. This collaborative effort is estimated to span over a span of 2 months with the guidance of Chartered Electrical Engineers and Senior Lecturers of Engineering Faculties. The proper training will be provided. Volunteers who contribute sufficiently will receive letters of appreciation mentioning the trainings they have accomplished.

We extend a warm invitation to you to be a part of this dynamic group, contributing to the preparation of drawings and the collection of vital data.

_Google form Link: https://forms.gle/yYbHLfMTm9FEwDS97_

Submission Deadline: 9:00 PM, September 14th, 2023.

Warm Regards,
EETESC of IESL

10/2/23, 11:59 PM - SHOBIJAN: ‼️‼️‼️‼️‼️‼️‼️‼️‼️‼️‼️
Hello everyone,

Civil & Environmental Engineering Society of University of Jaffna successfully published the second issue of the Nail magazine last week. And next issue of the magazine will be published in January 2024, If you’re interested in contributing an article for the next issue of the magazine, you can write articles on any topic, preferably related to engineering. You can also submit your digital artwork and photographs with a context related to engineering. The editorial panel will choose quality works  for publication. 

Here are some guidelines for submitting your work:
*•* Articles should be around 2500 (Min 2000) words and should be written in English 
*•* Your artwork can be in any medium, but it should be created digitally. If you want to submit a non-digital drawing, send it as a scanned file or as a photograph
*•* Photographs should be high resolution (at least 300 dpi) and in jpeg or png format
*•* Please include a brief bio and a headshot with your photograph submission. 
*•* All submitted works will be reviewed by the editorial panel
*•* You can submit your work anytime before *15th of November 2023* and we will review your submission and get back to you as soon as possible. 

Previous issues and current issue of the Nail can be viewed here:
https://publication.jfn.ac.lk/nail/

For further information, you can contact 
Vinojan P. 0775003347

Serving on the Executive Committee is a fantastic way to contribute to our vibrant IEEE community, shape the future of our branch, and develop valuable leadership skills. We are seeking passionate individuals with a commitment to excellence and a vision for driving our IEEE-SB-UoJ forward.

https://bit.ly/volunteer_handbook_2024

Thank you for considering this opportunity, and we eagerly anticipate your valuable contributions to the IEEE Student Branch of the University of Jaffna.

Varsha

2/10/24, 10:04 AM - Pramuda (මටා) Aiya E21 UOJ: Dear  Students,
                We are pleased to announce the availability of studentships to assist those facing financial challenges in pursuing their education. The deadline for application submission is March 4, 2024, at 11.59 pm. All enrolled students experiencing financial hardship are eligible to apply. Current recipients of financial support are also required to submit the application form to ensure the continuity of their assistance; failure to do so may result in a pause or termination of current support. The application process involves two steps: firstly, fill and certify the form with Grama Niladhari, and secondly, complete the online application, including uploading the signed form. For any clarifications or assistance, please contact me at mayooran@eng.jfn.ac.lk. We encourage all eligible students to take advantage of this opportunity for financial aid.


Application Process:

The application process involves two steps:

Application Form Submission:
Fill out the application form available at http://tinyurl.com/4wauatmh or simply scan the QR Code given below.
Certify all information by visiting your local Grama Niladhari. 
Online Application Submission:
Fill out the online application http://tinyurl.com/3w25fnt8 or simply scan the QR Code given below and upload the signed form as part of the process.

Submit the form in person at the AR Office (which is located on the ground floor of the admin building).

2/28/24, 6:49 AM - Jenarththan Akilan: Attention Engineering Students!

Express Your Interest in Building the Future of Entrepreneurship at University of Jaffna

Are you passionate about innovation, leadership, and creating your own path in the business world? Join us in laying the foundation for the Entrepreneurship Club at the University of Jaffna, Faculty of Engineering!

Why Join the Entrepreneurship Club?

* Networking Opportunities: Connect with like-minded individuals, mentors, and industry professionals who share your passion for entrepreneurship.
* Skill Development: Sharpen your entrepreneurial skills through workshops, seminars, and hands-on activities designed to foster creativity, problem-solving, and strategic thinking.
* Collaborative Projects: Work on real-world projects, startup ventures, and competitions that challenge you to apply your knowledge and make a tangible impact.
* Resource Access: Gain access to resources, funding opportunities, and support networks to help turn your ideas into successful ventures.
* Community Engagement: Engage with the local community through outreach initiatives, partnerships, and events that promote entrepreneurship and innovation.

Express Your Interest Today!

If you're ready to embark on an exciting journey of entrepreneurship and make a difference in the world, we want to hear from you! Express your interest by filling out the form below:

https://forms.gle/xmw9XQqFw1gTiQHfA

Date & Location:
Date: 28 FEBRUARY 2024 : 4.30 PM
Location: MECHANICAL ENGINEERING LECTUER HALL

For more information, contact us at +94776950774 (Kajenthiran - Manager / Incubation Center).

Don't miss this opportunity to be a part of something extraordinary! Join the Entrepreneurship Club and let's create a future filled with innovation, growth, and endless possibilities.

Together, let's build the future of entrepreneurship at University of Jaffna, Faculty of Engineering!

10/6/24, 1:14 PM - Lukmasinghe (ගොයියා) Aiya E21 UOJ: Dear Student Budding Entrepreneur, 

We are excited to invite you to an upcoming Northern Province Workshop on “How to Prepare a Pitch Deck”, part of the IEEE Innovation Nation Sri Lanka 2024 series. This workshop will provide valuable insights and practical tips to help you create compelling pitch decks, a critical skill for pitching business ideas, projects, or research in any field.

Event Details:

Date: 6th of October 2024
Time: 7:00 PM
Platform: Zoom
Speakers:

Mr. Dimuthu Anuraj – Founding Chairman of the IEEE Student Branch of the University of Jaffna and Global IEEE Volunteer
Mr. Anu Rakavan – Manager, University Business Linkage, University of Jaffna
During this session, you will gain:

A comprehensive understanding of the elements of a great pitch deck.
Tips on how to tailor your presentation to investors or evaluators.
Examples and success stories from the speakers’ experiences.
Why Attend?

This webinar is crucial for anyone aiming to participate in IEEE Innovation Nation Sri Lanka 2024, a prestigious competition that fosters entrepreneurial and innovative thinking.
Competitors will have the opportunity to pitch their ideas and potentially secure funding or resources to bring them to life!
Don’t miss out on this unique opportunity to enhance your pitching skills and boost your chances in the IEEE Innovation Nation competition.

10/18/24, 6:37 PM - Shathurjan: 🚨 Attention Innovators & Problem-Solvers! 🚨

🌟 Are you ready to dive into the future of prosthetics? 🌟

Join us for the Innovative 3D Printed Solutions for Upper Limb Prosthetics Hackathon and showcase your creativity and engineering skills. Whether you’re passionate about design, 3D printing, or creating impactful solutions, this is the perfect chance to make a real difference!

💡 What are the challenges to solve?
* Replicate existing 3D-printed prosthetics or create your own innovative designs!
* Work on ergonomic, functional, and user-friendly prosthetics.
* Research and choose the best materials to balance durability, flexibility, and comfort.
* Bonus challenge: Develop methods to personalize prosthetics for individual needs! 🙌

🛠️ Prize: A part-time internship at the 3D Printing Lab 💼 — the ideal stepping stone for your career!

📅 Deadline to register: 22nd October 2024
💥 Registration fee: FREE!

Outcome and deliverables are the priority! 💯
